40:05.236 --> 40:08.506 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Our William Brangham is
reporting near the
Standing Rock Reservation.

40:08.539 --> 40:13.578 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I spoke to him a short time ago
and asked
him what the immediate reaction
was like today.

40:13.611 --> 40:17.649 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Yes, this has
been a day
that nobody here really wanted
to see happen.

40:17.682 --> 40:19.550 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't know if you can see
behind me, but
this is the camp.

40:19.584 --> 40:22.920 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
This is the main area where
people have been
gathering for weeks, and this is
the worst

40:22.954 --> 40:24.722 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
possible news initially.

40:24.756 --> 40:27.859 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Interestingly, the word is
slowly starting
to trickle out.

40:27.892 --> 40:31.829 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I mean, in fact, many people I
talked to this
afternoon, I was the one telling
them the

40:31.863 --> 40:35.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
news about the hearing, because
the cell phone
service here is really bad, and
so people

40:35.600 --> 40:38.936 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are not getting the news as
quickly as some
of us are.

40:38.970 --> 40:42.240 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the general sense was that
people were
really disappointed.

40:42.273 --> 40:44.142 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There's been a sense of
resignation.

40:44.175 --> 40:47.812 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Many people feared that this
would be the
judge's ruling, that they
thought that the

40:47.845 --> 40:51.015 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Corps would be allowed to do
this and that
the energy company would be
allowed to put

40:51.049 --> 40:52.950 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the pipeline in.

40:52.984 --> 40:57.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When the news also came that the
Justice Department
is considering stepping in and
putting a stop

40:57.255 --> 41:00.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to this, that only gave people a
certain level
of hope.

41:00.591 --> 41:05.229 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The people that I talked to said
they think
this is going to be an ongoing,
protracted

41:05.263 --> 41:08.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
battle for weeks, months, maybe
years to come.

41:08.399 --> 41:11.436 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: William,
specifically, what
is the tribe's complaint?

41:11.469 --> 41:16.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The principal
argument the
Standing Rock Tribe has is that
the construction

41:16.974 --> 41:22.013 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of this pipeline is going to do,
one, it's
going to destroy a lot of very,
very important

41:22.046 --> 41:28.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
cultural sites to them, burial
grounds, historic
meeting places for their people,
and, number

41:28.353 --> 41:33.691 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
two, that the pipeline, which,
although it
is not going to go through
tribal lands, it

41:33.725 --> 41:35.793 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is just a short distance away.

41:35.827 --> 41:38.096 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The pipeline will go underneath
the river.

41:38.129 --> 41:41.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And many people are concerned
that if a pipeline
that is carrying hundreds of
thousands of

41:41.999 --> 41:46.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
gallons of oil goes underneath
the river,
that there could be some sort of
a rupture

41:46.270 --> 41:51.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and, if that happens, that might
spill oil
into their primary source of
drinking water.

41:51.409 --> 41:54.545 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so that's been the main
concern, that
the construction of the pipeline
is going

41:54.579 --> 41:59.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to destroy lands that are very,
very important
to them and that the potential
for contamination

41:59.217 --> 42:01.052 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
is enormous.

42:01.085 --> 42:05.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: This would be a
very significant
pipeline, carrying about half of
current Bakken

42:05.189 --> 42:06.157 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
oil production.

42:06.190 --> 42:07.992 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How is the industry responding?

42:08.025 --> 42:11.262 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: The company
that is building
the pipeline has argued all
along that they

42:11.295 --> 42:15.566 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
followed the rules, they filled
out the right
permits, they got all the right
permissions,

42:15.600 --> 42:18.970 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they did the proper surveys, and
that they
have broken no laws whatsoever.

42:19.003 --> 42:21.406 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In fact, that's not really been
the allegation
thus far.

42:21.439 --> 42:25.510 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The tribe's main concern has
been with the
Army Corps of Engineers, who
granted one of

42:25.543 --> 42:27.445 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the main permits for the
pipeline to go in.

42:27.478 --> 42:30.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the Corps says too that they
did all the
proper consultations.

42:30.615 --> 42:36.888 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the oil company argues also
that they
think this is an important
economic engine

42:36.921 --> 42:38.790 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for the area.

42:38.823 --> 42:42.560 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They say there will be jobs in
construction
of the pipeline, jobs in
maintaining the pipeline,

42:42.593 --> 42:47.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and that they say, look, we
still live in
an oil-based society, and if oil
needs to

42:47.231 --> 42:52.870 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
get from the Bakken oil fields
to market,
this pipeline is the delivery
device for that.

42:52.904 --> 42:56.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: It seems there
are really
two parts to this fight, the
court battle

42:56.641 --> 42:58.276 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and on-the-ground protests.

42:58.309 --> 43:00.244 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
William, explain what happens
now in each.

43:00.278 --> 43:03.681 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: Obviously,
with regards
to the courts, who knows how
that's going

43:03.714 --> 43:04.849 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to play out.

43:04.882 --> 43:06.617 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Justice Department may step
in forcefully
on this.

43:06.651 --> 43:08.553 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We will have to wait and see on
that.

43:08.586 --> 43:13.124 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
As far as what happens here on
the ground,
we have heard from some people
who've said,

43:13.157 --> 43:17.094 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
regardless of what happens with
the courts,
with the rulings, with the Army
Corps, there

43:17.128 --> 43:21.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is a certain group of people
here who argue
they will do everything that
they can to not

43:21.065 --> 43:22.934 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
let this pipeline go forward.

43:22.967 --> 43:28.239 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have heard people talking
about the possibility
of physically putting themselves
in the way

43:28.272 --> 43:31.709 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the construction equipment,
in the way
of the workers' camps.

43:31.742 --> 43:34.712 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And how widespread that
sentiment is, I don't
really know.

43:34.745 --> 43:39.183 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we will see in the next days
and weeks,
if the construction really does
take off,

43:39.217 --> 43:40.985 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
whether or not those actions
come true.

43:41.018 --> 43:45.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there is a minority of
people here, at
least, that will do everything
they possibly

43:45.490 --> 43:47.425 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
can to try to stop this from
going forward.

43:47.458 --> 43:51.929 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LISA DESJARDINS: Our William
Brangham, speaking
with us from North Dakota, thank
you.

43:51.963 --> 44:01.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we look forward to seeing
your reports
in coming days.

44:01.038 --> 44:14.752 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And, finally,
some thoughts
as we approach, on Sunday, the
15th anniversary

44:14.785 --> 44:16.587 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of the 9/11 attacks.

44:16.621 --> 44:21.492 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are national memorials at
three sites.

44:21.526 --> 44:26.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In New York City, the World
Trade Center Memorial
attracts millions of visitors.

44:26.631 --> 44:32.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Two reflecting pools inscribed
with the names
of the nearly 3,000 people who
died in all

44:32.970 --> 44:37.542 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the attacks sit in the
footprint of the
original Twin Towers.

44:37.575 --> 44:40.211 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There's also a museum and a
park.

44:40.244 --> 44:46.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Pentagon Memorial is off the
beaten path,
located directly behind the
building.

44:46.150 --> 44:53.391 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It has small benches poised
above lighted
pools to remember the 184 people
who died

44:53.424 --> 44:59.597 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
at the Pentagon and on American
Airlines Flight
77 that crashed into it.

44:59.630 --> 45:05.803 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Shanksville, Pennsylvania,
the memorial
is in a remote field, set upon
the crash site

45:05.836 --> 45:08.172 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of Flight 93.

45:08.205 --> 45:14.378 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have a collection now of
voices, including
family members, visitors and
writers, who

45:14.412 --> 45:18.149 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
share their thoughts on the
meaning of these
memorials.

45:18.182 --> 45:25.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LARRY CONOVER: I think it's a
memory that
all of us will carry with us all
of our lives.

45:25.222 --> 45:29.093 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I know my parents' generation,
they thought
of Pearl Harbor.

45:29.126 --> 45:31.629 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That was kind of a signal moment
for them.

45:31.662 --> 45:37.101 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For my generation, it was this
tragic event
that happened here on 9/11.

45:37.134 --> 45:46.077 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
LORETTA VARGAS: From the
devastation, to how
it looks right now, it just --
it's a meditation

45:46.110 --> 45:47.445 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
for me.

45:47.478 --> 45:51.816 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I'm just in my space of
gratitude that
I'm here.

45:51.849 --> 45:55.586 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAUL GOLDBERGER, "Vanity
FairÂ®MD-BO /": The
most powerful thing of all about
the site

45:55.620 --> 46:04.095 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
is the void, the sense that
there, where these
incredibly tall, strong
buildings stood, is

46:04.128 --> 46:06.664 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
just emptiness now.

46:06.697 --> 46:07.732 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But there are also the names.

46:07.765 --> 46:09.867 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
The names are a remembrance.

46:09.900 --> 46:16.273 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They are a sign that those
people who are
gone will be remembered
permanently.

46:16.307 --> 46:20.911 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And then there is water, which
is a sign of
renewal and nature.

46:20.945 --> 46:27.718 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The sound of the waterfall
drowning out the
sounds of the city is also very,
very important,

46:27.752 --> 46:31.255 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
because it helps take you into
another place
when you're there.

46:31.288 --> 46:36.394 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DANA ORR: I'm so proud of the
city for not,
you know, putting something new,
like, right

46:36.427 --> 46:37.895 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in this spot.

46:37.928 --> 46:41.098 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Like, I understand that the fact
that there
needed to be another building.

46:41.132 --> 46:43.968 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I understand that life goes on.

46:44.001 --> 46:49.840 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I am just -- I'm so proud
that this memorial
is not only here, but it's as
big.

46:49.874 --> 46:55.780 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PAUL GOLDBERGER: In New York,
the memorial
at Ground Zero had a particular
challenge,

46:55.813 --> 47:01.719 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to allow that entire 16 acres to
have been
a memorial.

47:01.752 --> 47:08.225 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
